<section xml:id="lesson-07">
  <title>Lesson 7 - Quadratic Equations</title>

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>Solve quadratic equations by factoring.</li>
      <li>Solve quadratic equations using the square root property.</li>
      <li>Solve quadratic equations by completing the square.</li>
      <li>Solve quadratic equations using the quadratic formula.</li>
      <li>Use the discriminant to analyze the number and type of solutions.</li>
      <li>Solve application problems involving quadratic equations.</li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="l7-factoring">
    <title>Solving by Factoring</title>

      <exercise xml:id="l7-ex1">
        <statement>
          <p>Solve the following equations by factoring.</p>
          <ol marker="a.">
            <li><m>15x^2 + 4x - 4 = 0</m></li>
            <li><m>x^2 - 64 = 0</m></li>
            <li><m>2x^2 - 14 = -3x</m></li>
          </ol>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>Rewrite each equation in standard form, factor, and solve.</p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="l7-square-root">
    <title>Square Root Property</title>

      <exercise xml:id="l7-ex2">
        <statement>
          <p>Solve the following equations by the square root property.</p>
          <ol marker="a.">
            <li><m>x^2 - 12 = 0</m></li>
            <li><m>(x - 6)^2 - 10 = 39</m></li>
          </ol>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>Isolate the squared term, then apply the square root property.</p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="l7-completing-square">
    <title>Completing the Square</title>

      <exercise xml:id="l7-ex3">
        <statement>
          <p>Solve the following equations by completing the square.</p>
          <ol marker="a.">
            <li><m>6x^2 - 48 = -12x</m></li>
            <li><m>2x^2 - 5x + 67 = 0</m></li>
          </ol>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>Rewrite each equation and complete the square to solve.</p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="l7-quadratic-formula">
    <title>Quadratic Formula</title>

      <exercise xml:id="l7-ex4">
        <statement>
          <p>Solve the following equations using the quadratic formula.</p>
          <ol marker="a.">
            <li><m>2x^2 - 7x - 13 = -10</m></li>
            <li><m>x^2 - 6x + 12 = 0</m></li>
          </ol>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>Write each equation in standard form and apply the quadratic formula.</p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="l7-discriminant">
    <title>Using the Discriminant</title>

      <exercise xml:id="l7-ex5">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Use the discriminant to determine the number and character of the solutions.
          </p>
          <ol marker="a.">
            <li><m>-10x^2 - 3x - 9 = -2x</m></li>
            <li><m>2x^2 = 10x + 5</m></li>
            <li><m>-7x^2 + 16x = 8x</m></li>
            <li><m>4x^2 + 8x + 4 = 0</m></li>
          </ol>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>Rewrite in standard form and evaluate the discriminant.</p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="l7-application">
    <title>Quadratic Application</title>

      <exercise xml:id="l7-ex6">
        <statement>
          <p>
            The weekly revenue for a particular museum is estimated by
            <m>r = -2.5p^2 + 187p</m>, where <m>p</m> is the price of a single ticket.
            Determine the ticket price that produces a weekly revenue of
            <m>\$2500</m>.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>Set the revenue equation equal to 2500 and solve the resulting quadratic.</p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
  </subsection>

</section>